    "notes": "Gatefold cover pressed at Columbia Carrollton pressing plant (identified by G1 in runouts). One side appears to use metal parts sourced from Columbia Terre Haute (T1 in runout). Labels printed with \"18\" which would normally indicate a Presswell pressing, but Columbia House typically used labels sourced from other pressing plants.\n\nSome copies have a white CRC sticker on back cover.\n\nAll tracks recorded live during Rush's 1981 world tour.\nSides A, C, and D were recorded in Canada by Le Mobile and the Record Plant Mobile.\nSide B was recorded in the UK by Mobile One.\n\n\n",
